Pre-Game Insights: India and the Netherlands will play the 23rd match of the T20 World Cup 2022 on Thursday (October 27) at the Sydney Cricket Ground.
This will be the second game of the Super-12 stage for both teams.
India defeated Pakistan in their first game as they chased the target of 160 runs on the last delivery of the game.
Virat Kohli won the Player of the Match award and played one of his best innings in the shortest format of the game.
The Netherlands, on the other hand, lost their opening game of the Super-12 stage against Bangladesh by a mere margin of nine runs.
